[1
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 1998 11:19:35 -0500
From: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>
Source: Eurosurveillance Weekly, week 23, June 3rd, 1998

Incidence of new variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in the United Kingdom:
June update.
Twenty-six definite and probable cases of new variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob
disease had been identified in the United Kingdom by the end of April, 1998
(1). One of the definite cases is still alive (1).
References:
1.Monthly Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease figures. Department of Health, press
release 1 June 1998 <http://www.coi.gov.uk/coi/depts/GDH/coi2139e.ok>
Reported by Stuart Handysides (shandysi@phls.co.uk), PHLS Communicable
Disease Surveillance Centre, London England.
--
